  "body": "assume I have a rc.yaml\r\n``` console\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: ReplicationController\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: test-rc\r\n  labels:\r\n    name: foo\r\nspec:\r\n  ....\r\n```\r\nwhen I run `apply` first time to create this resource, like `kubectl apply -f rc.yaml -o yaml`\r\nthe output I got is the resource same as live object, with annotations.\r\n```console\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: ReplicationController\r\nmetadata:\r\n  annotations:\r\n    kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration: |\r\n      {\"apiVersion\":\"v1\",\"kind\":\"ReplicationController\",\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{},\"labels\":{\"name\":\"foo\"}\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut if I change the rc.yaml like change the label  `name: foo`  to `name: bar`  then run \r\n`kubectl apply -f rc.yaml -o yaml` \r\nthe output I got is still  `name: foo` in annotations. \r\n```console\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: ReplicationController\r\nmetadata:\r\n  annotations:\r\n    kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration: |\r\n      {\"apiVersion\":\"v1\",\"kind\":\"ReplicationController\",\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{},\"labels\":{\"name\":\"foo\"},\r\n```\r\nshould the last time `-o yaml` output to be live object in server ?\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-cli-bugs  @pwittrock @AdoHe \r\n",
